n feminism reveals the possibility of a just world beyond the carceral state, which is fundamentally unable to respond to, let alone remedy, harm. As Imperfect Victims shows, abolition feminism is the only politics and practice that can undo the indescribable damage inflicted on survivors by the very system purporting to protect them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAbused womenxLegal status, laws, etc2DLC. 0aAbused womenxLegal status, laws, etc. 0aFeminism2DLC. 0aFeminism. 0aIntimate partner violencezUnited States2DLC. 0aIntimate partner violencezUnited States. 0aPrison abolition movementszUnited States2DLC. 0aPrison abolition movementszUnited States. 0aVictims of family violencexLegal status, laws, etc2DLC. 0aVictims of family violencexLegal status, laws, etc. 0aWomen prisonersxCrimes against2DLC. 0aWomen prisonersxCrimes against. 0aWomen prisonersxLegal status, laws, etc2DLC. 0aWomen prisonersxLegal status, laws, etc. 7aLAW / Criminal Law / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishz978311131914808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023z9783111318226oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520391130?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520391130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520391130/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131914-8  EBOOK 